abstract.text: Jumps playback on the current track to the desired timestamp as soon as possible.
This will mix the track with itself so the skip is as little noticeable as possible and does so beatmatched, which means the landing position will be close but not exactly the fed timestamp.
If on, after a playlist is done it restarts. Otherwise, it pauses.
This defaults to false on initialisation and should be set to match the state of the consumerâ€™s UI
Sets a new order to the playlist while continuing to play the current track
Removes a track from a playlist in Automix SDK at a given index.
If the index is out of bounds it does nothing.
Makes the Automix SDK play a given track until the end and then pause. If you run this on the last track it will fail.
If on, after a playlist is done it restarts. Otherwise, it pauses.
Pauses playback if playing.
If already paused it does nothing.
Sets the Automix SDK play speed to a given value between 0.5 and 2. 0.5 is playback at half speed, 2 is playback aty double speed
Sets the Automix SDK volume to a given value between 0 and 1. If muted, calling this will cause AutomixSDK to unmute.
Makes Automix SDK stop looping the currently playing track
Moves the track at index to a different index
Starts playback if paused.
If already playing it does nothing.
Jumps playback on the current track to the desired timestamp as soon as possible.
This will mix the track with itself so the skip is as little noticeable as possible and does so beatmatched, which means the landing position will be close but not exactly the fed timestamp.
Makes Automix SDK loop the currently playing track
Loads a new playlist into Automix SDK.
If the playlist is empty this opperation will fail and Automix SDK will be turned off
This will stop playback of the playlist currently playing and start the new one.
AutomixSDK represents the Automix SDK and exposes all its functionality. It follows a Singleton pattern.
Provide seamless transitions between tracks and beat-matched seek experience within your music player application in iOS, iPad.
Makes playback go to the beginning of the current track
Adds a track to a playlist in Automix SDK at a given index.
If the index is out of bounds it does nothing.
Sets the Automix SDK tempo to a given value between 0 and 1. 0 is -15% and 1 is +15%.
Adds set track to a playlist in Automix SDK at a given index.
If the index is out of bounds it does nothing.
Toggles the Automix SDK mute
Makes playback go to the beginning of the previuous track
Mixes in the next track as soon as possible, when the mix transition ends, the currently playin gtrack becomes the next track in the playlist.
Depending on how well the contiguous tracks mix together, the mix Automix SDK generates may be long - This is expected and even desired behaviour, but without some UI
It may be confusing to an end user - The next track will not become the currently playing one until mixing is over.
Jumps playback on the beginning of the track at the desired index as soon as possible.
Sets the Automix SDK mute
